# Dataset

The original Flipkart review dataset is **not included** in this repository due to GitHub file size limitations and licensing considerations.

## Dataset Source

This project uses the **Flipkart Product Reviews Dataset** available on Kaggle (Link : https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/mansithummar67/flipkart-product-review-dataset)

Download the dataset from Kaggle and place it inside the `data/` directory.

```
data/
└── flipkart_product.csv
```

The cleaning pipeline expects the input file to be named:

```
flipkart_product.csv
```

---

# Expected Columns

The raw dataset should contain the following columns:

| Column | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| ProductName | Product title |
| Price | Product price |
| Rate | Customer rating (1–5) |
| Review | Full customer review |
| Summary | Review summary |

---

# Generate the Cleaned Dataset

Run the data cleaning pipeline:

```bash
python src/01_data_cleaning.py data/flipkart_product.csv data/flipkart_cleaned_final.csv
```

This script performs:

- Character encoding repair
- Duplicate removal
- Missing value handling
- Price and rating normalization
- Brand extraction
- Product categorization
- Category grouping
- Review text cleaning
- VADER sentiment analysis
- Rating–Sentiment mismatch detection

The cleaned dataset (`flipkart_cleaned_final.csv`) is generated automatically and serves as the input for SQL analysis and the Power BI dashboard.

---

# Dataset Statistics

After cleaning, the dataset contains approximately:

- **162,183 customer reviews**
- Product categories across Electronics, Fashion, Home, Beauty, Sports, Books, and more
- Engineered features for business intelligence and NLP analysis

